Ordered over $100 worth of food. I ordered lobster gumbo.... yeah I was excited . Got crawfish instead . no problem stuff happens but it was a mistake so I called to get my money for that specific item back. The woman who answered the phone was extremely rude. At first they said what was in my gumbo was lobster ... then they said that the chef read it wrong and when I asked her to explain because at first she made it sound like I ordered crawfish, instead of just telling me what she meant she decided to yell at me over the phone. “LISTEN TO ME!” and then continued to yell her explanation. I understand customer service is tough , I’ve done it. But when someone’s your costumer and they spent over $100... yeah I’m all set. Absolutely disgusting behavior.

The staff, however, speaks limited English but enough to understand your order and make fantastic recommendations.  The food is from the Dominican Republic.  Staff is very proud and eager to educate you about their culture...very welcoming and friendly....

There were a lot of Puerto Rican items on the menu (and interestingly all around this town) and I wasn't all that familiar with them so I sort of picked stuff randomly. The bartender was able to figure out what I wanted because I was pointing to the things we wanted. It was still so loud my wife and I could only communicate by texting each other on our phones. It made me laugh to think of people who complain about places being too noisy
